## Project Overview
This repo is managed with an issue-first workflow.
The agent should ask the user for missing business/project details when placeholders remain.

## GitHub Workflow (User-Managed Merges + Manual Issue Closing)
- Always read `GITHUB_ISSUES_GUIDE.md` before making any code changes.
- Every task requires a GitHub Issue. Ask for the Issue ID; if it doesn't exist, ask permission to create it.
- Branching:
  - Preferred: one branch per issue.
  - If you are using a fixed existing branch (per user instruction), do not create new branches; commit on the current branch.
- Commits:
  - All commit messages must reference the issue ID.
  - Format: `[#ISSUE_ID] Commit message`
- PR + Issue closing:
  - PR creation/merge and issue closing are handled manually by you (the user).

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode — avoid `any` unless unavoidable
- Functional components only
- Use `@/` aliases for internal imports
- Prefer `const` over `let`

## UI / Styling
- Tailwind first
- Use shadcn/ui primitives from `src/components/ui` (do not edit primitives directly)

## MCP Security Rules
- Never place token values into `.cursor/mcp.json`
- Tokens belong only in `.env.local` (local-only; never commit)

